verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Guide me, O Thou great Jehovah, pilgrim through this barren land;
I am weak, but Thou art mighty, hold me with Thy pow’rful hand.
Bread of heaven, Bread of heaven, feed me til I want no more;
Feed me till I want no more.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Open now the crystal fountain, whence the healing stream doth flow;
Let the fire and cloudy pillar lead me all my journey through.
Strong Deliv’rer, strong Deliv’rer, Be Thou still my strength and shield;
Be thou still my strength and shield.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}When I tread the verge of Jordan, bid my anxious fears subside;
Death of death and hell’s destruction land me safe on Canaan’s side.
Songs of praises, songs of praises I will ever give to Thee;
I will ever give to Thee.{/lang-eng}
